Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows hypoglycemia, elevated creatinine indicating impaired renal function, and significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting possible diabetic nephropathy or another renal pathology with poor glycemic control. Urine is cloudy, brown, and dilute, but without evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
